<DOC><DOCNO> AP881126-0082 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-26-88 1406EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Israel-HospitalFire     11-26 0115</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Israel-Hospital Fire,0119</SECOND><HEAD>Five Injured In Hospital Fire</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A fire broke out Saturday at Hadassah Hospitaland five policemen and firefighters who evacuated the patients wereinjured, authorities said.   No injuries were reported among the patients.   Police spokesman Rafi Levy and Hadassah officials said the firebroke out at the hospital's laundry. The smoke spread throughventilation openings and engulfed three floors, they said.   Fire brigades and emergency medical and police teams evacuatedpatients stationed at the damaged floors, fire brigade chief PinchasSuhami said.   The radio said two police officers and a firefighters wereinjured by smoke inhalation and two other firefighters by brokenglass.   The cause was under investigation.</TEXT></DOC>